WEBVTT

1
00:01:56.994 --> 00:01:59.246
- Easy. boy.
-

2
00:03:12.236 --> 00:03:14.279
What do you expect?
They're savages.

3
00:03:14.405 --> 00:03:16.782
One lot steals a goat from another lot.

4
00:03:16.907 --> 00:03:19.243
before you know it
they're ripping each other to pieces.

5
00:03:19.368 --> 00:03:21.829
I've never seen wildlings do a thing like this.

6
00:03:21.954 --> 00:03:24.123
I never seen a thing like this.
not ever in my life.

7
00:03:24.248 --> 00:03:26.417
How close did you get?

8
00:03:26.542 --> 00:03:29.962
- Close as any man would.
- We should head back to the Wall.

9
00:03:32.589 --> 00:03:34.049
Do the dead frighten you?

10
00:03:34.174 --> 00:03:36.301
Our orders were to track the wildlings.

11
00:03:36.427 --> 00:03:39.638
We tracked them.
They won't trouble us no more.

12
00:03:39.763 --> 00:03:42.182
You don't think he'll ask us how they died?

13
00:03:44.435 --> 00:03:46.228
Get back on your horse.

14
00:03:50.941 --> 00:03:53.444
Whatever did it to them
could do it to us.

15
00:03:53.569 --> 00:03:55.154
They even killed the children.

16
00:03:56.113 --> 00:03:58.115
It's a good thing we're not children.

17
00:03:59.491 --> 00:04:02.286
You want to run away south.
run away.

18
00:04:02.411 --> 00:04:05.330
Of course.
they will behead you as a deserter.

19
00:04:05.456 --> 00:04:07.583
If I don't catch you first.

20
00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:12.254
Get back on your horse.

21
00:04:12.379 --> 00:04:14.715
I won't say it again.

22
00:04:45.829 --> 00:04:48.332
Your dead men seem
to have moved camp.

23
00:04:49.041 --> 00:04:50.709
They were here.

24
00:04:54.087 --> 00:04:55.756
See where they went.

25
00:05:42.261 --> 00:05:44.137
What is it?

26
00:05:45.430 --> 00:05:46.557
It's...

27
00:09:49.633 --> 00:09:52.094
Go on. Father's watching.

28
00:09:54.304 --> 00:09:56.014
And your mother.

29
00:10:02.187 --> 00:10:05.524
Fine work. as always.
Well done.

30
00:10:05.649 --> 00:10:07.317
Thank you.

31
00:10:07.442 --> 00:10:11.279
I love the detail that you've managed
to get in these corners.

32
00:10:11.404 --> 00:10:13.198
Quite beautiful.

33
00:10:13.323 --> 00:10:15.200
The stitching...

34
00:10:15.325 --> 00:10:17.536
Oh. no. no. no. This stitch is very...

35
00:10:19.246 --> 00:10:21.206
- It's beautiful.
- Thank you.

36
00:10:36.388 --> 00:10:39.141
And which one of you
was a marksman at ten?

37
00:10:40.183 --> 00:10:41.685
Keep practicing. Bran.

38
00:10:43.854 --> 00:10:45.814
Go on.

39
00:10:45.939 --> 00:10:48.608
Don't think too much. Bran.

40
00:10:51.027 --> 00:10:52.195
Relax your bow arm.

41
00:11:05.333 --> 00:11:06.835
- Quick. Bran!
- Faster.

42
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:10.422
Lord Stark!

43
00:11:12.465 --> 00:11:13.508
My lady.

44
00:11:14.551 --> 00:11:16.761
A guardsman just rode in from the hills.

45
00:11:16.887 --> 00:11:19.890
They've captured a deserter
from the Night's Watch.

46
00:11:23.185 --> 00:11:25.312
Get the lads to saddle their horses.

47
00:11:25.437 --> 00:11:27.397
Do you have to?

48
00:11:27.522 --> 00:11:29.608
He swore an oath. Cat.

49
00:11:29.733 --> 00:11:31.735
Law is law. my lady.

50
00:11:32.736 --> 00:11:34.821
Tell Bran he's coming too.

51
00:11:36.740 --> 00:11:38.325
Ned.

52
00:11:38.450 --> 00:11:40.744
Ten is too young
to see such things.

53
00:11:40.869 --> 00:11:42.412
He won't be a boy forever.

54
00:11:44.414 --> 00:11:46.082
And winter is coming.

55
00:12:05.227 --> 00:12:07.437
Good lad. go run back and get the rest.

56
00:12:13.568 --> 00:12:15.153
White walkers.

57
00:12:15.278 --> 00:12:17.989
I saw the white walkers.

58
00:12:18.114 --> 00:12:19.991
White walkers.

59
00:12:20.116 --> 00:12:23.161
The white walkers. I saw them.

60
00:12:31.962 --> 00:12:33.588
I know I broke my oath.

61
00:12:34.798 --> 00:12:36.299
And I know I'm a deserter.

62
00:12:37.175 --> 00:12:39.844
I should have gone back to the Wall
and warned them. but...

63
00:12:41.012 --> 00:12:43.014
I saw what I saw.

64
00:12:43.139 --> 00:12:44.683
I saw the white walkers.

65
00:12:46.643 --> 00:12:48.478
People need to Know.

66
00:12:50.647 --> 00:12:52.482
If you can get word to my family...

67
00:12:52.607 --> 00:12:54.901
tell them I'm no coward.

68
00:12:55.026 --> 00:12:56.987
Tell them I'm sorry.

69
00:13:14.004 --> 00:13:15.672
Forgive me. Lord.

70
00:13:20.051 --> 00:13:22.220
In the name of Robert
of the House Baratheon.

71
00:13:22.345 --> 00:13:24.306
- the first of his name...
- Don't look away.

72
00:13:24.431 --> 00:13:27.267
- ...King of the Andals and the First Men...
- Father will know if you do.

73
00:13:27.392 --> 00:13:30.729
...Lord of the Seven Kingdoms
and protector of the realm.

74
00:13:30.854 --> 00:13:33.732
I
 Eddard of the House Stark.

75
00:13:33.857 --> 00:13:36.401
Lord of Winterfell
and Warden of the North.

76
00:13:36.526 --> 00:13:38.987
sentence you to die.

77
00:13:53.793 --> 00:13:55.462
You did well.

78
00:14:23.656 --> 00:14:25.116
You understand why I did it?

79
00:14:25.241 --> 00:14:27.118
Jon said he was a deserter.

80
00:14:27.243 --> 00:14:29.788
But do you understand
why I had to kill him?

81
00:14:29.913 --> 00:14:31.539
"Our way is the old way"?

82
00:14:33.166 --> 00:14:36.836
The man who passes the sentence
should swing the sword.

83
00:14:37.879 --> 00:14:40.256
Is it true he saw the white walkers?

84
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.261
The white walkers have been gone
for thousands of years.

85
00:14:46.429 --> 00:14:47.931
So he was lying?

86
00:14:52.435 --> 00:14:54.771
A madman sees what he sees.

87
00:15:20.713 --> 00:15:22.632
What is it?

88
00:15:25.009 --> 00:15:26.678
Mountain lion?

89
00:15:28.054 --> 00:15:30.390
There are no mountain lions
in these woods.

90
00:16:16.561 --> 00:16:18.354
I's a freak.

91
00:16:19.731 --> 00:16:21.024
It's a direwolf.

92
00:16:30.283 --> 00:16:32.535
Tough old beast.

93
00:16:34.829 --> 00:16:36.915
There are no direwolves
south of the Wall.

94
00:16:37.790 --> 00:16:39.083
Now there are five.

95
00:16:40.710 --> 00:16:42.378
You want to hold it?

96
00:16:46.925 --> 00:16:48.426
Where will they go?

97
00:16:48.551 --> 00:16:50.261
Their mother's dead.

98
00:16:50.386 --> 00:16:51.930
They don't belong down here.

99
00:16:52.055 --> 00:16:55.850
Better a quick death.
They won't last without their mother.

100
00:16:55.975 --> 00:16:57.977
- Right. Give it here.
- No!

101
00:16:58.102 --> 00:16:59.771
Put away your blade.

102
00:16:59.896 --> 00:17:02.815
- I take orders from your father. not you.
- Please. Father!

103
00:17:02.941 --> 00:17:04.734
I'm sorry. Bran.

104
00:17:04.859 --> 00:17:05.902
Lord Stark?

105
00:17:07.695 --> 00:17:09.197
There are five pups.

106
00:17:10.573 --> 00:17:12.659
One for each of the Stark children.

107
00:17:12.784 --> 00:17:15.286
The direwolf is the sigil of your house.

108
00:17:16.663 --> 00:17:18.873
They were meant to have them.

109
00:17:24.128 --> 00:17:26.297
You will train them yourselves.

110
00:17:26.422 --> 00:17:28.299
You will feed them yourselves.

111
00:17:28.424 --> 00:17:31.302
And if they die. you will bury them yourselves.

112
00:17:39.936 --> 00:17:41.646
What about you?

113
00:17:42.522 --> 00:17:44.190
I'm not a Stark.

114
00:17:44.315 --> 00:17:46.401
Get on.

115
00:17:56.452 --> 00:17:57.912
What is it?

116
00:18:02.125 --> 00:18:05.628
The runt of the litter.
That one's yours. Snow.

117
00:19:05.813 --> 00:19:08.983
As your brother.
I feel it's my duty to warn you...

118
00:19:10.234 --> 00:19:12.236
you worry too much.

119
00:19:12.362 --> 00:19:15.698
- It's starting to show.
- And you never worry about anything.

120
00:19:16.991 --> 00:19:20.912
When we were seven and you jumped off
the cliffs at Casterly Rock.

121
00:19:21.037 --> 00:19:25.416
100-foot drop into the water...
you were never afraid.

122
00:19:25.541 --> 00:19:28.169
There was nothing to be afraid of
until you told Father.

123
00:19:28.294 --> 00:19:31.881
"We're Lannisters.
Lannisters don't act like fools."

124
00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:37.845
- What if Jon Arryn told someone?
- But who would he tell?

125
00:19:39.222 --> 00:19:40.348
My husband.

126
00:19:40.473 --> 00:19:44.227
If he told the king. both our heads would be
skewered on the city gates by now.

127
00:19:45.770 --> 00:19:48.898
Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know.
it died with him.

128
00:19:49.774 --> 00:19:51.609
And Robert will choose
a new Hand of the King.

129
00:19:51.734 --> 00:19:55.321
someone to do his job while he's off
fucking boars and hunting whores.

130
00:19:55.446 --> 00:19:57.115
Or is it the other way around?

131
00:19:58.658 --> 00:20:00.993
And life will go on.

132
00:20:01.119 --> 00:20:03.705
You should be the Hand of the King.

133
00:20:04.580 --> 00:20:06.416
That's an honor I can do without.

134
00:20:06.541 --> 00:20:08.167
Their days are too long.

135
00:20:08.292 --> 00:20:09.961
their lives are too short.

136
00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:50.710
All these years.

137
00:20:50.835 --> 00:20:53.963
and I still feel like an outsider
when I come here.

138
00:20:55.798 --> 00:20:57.467
You have five northern children.

139
00:20:58.718 --> 00:21:01.012
You're not an outsider.

140
00:21:01.137 --> 00:21:03.639
I wonder if the old gods agree.

141
00:21:04.891 --> 00:21:06.768
It's your gods with all the rules.

142
00:21:13.524 --> 00:21:15.860

am so sorry. my love.

143
00:21:16.986 --> 00:21:20.615
- Tell me.
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

144
00:21:22.742 --> 00:21:24.285
Jon Arryn is dead.

145
00:21:24.410 --> 00:21:26.913
A fever took him.

146
00:21:29.832 --> 00:21:31.959
I know he was like a father to you.

147
00:21:35.087 --> 00:21:38.132
- Your sister. the boy?
- They both have their health.

148
00:21:38.257 --> 00:21:40.259
gods be good.

149
00:21:50.520 --> 00:21:51.854
The raven brought more news.

150
00:21:53.981 --> 00:21:56.359
The king rides for Winterfell...

151
00:21:57.401 --> 00:22:00.196
with the queen and all the rest of them.

152
00:22:01.113 --> 00:22:03.449
If he's coming this far north...

153
00:22:05.117 --> 00:22:07.036
there's only one thing he's after.

154
00:22:07.161 --> 00:22:10.540
You can always say no. Ned.

155
00:22:18.881 --> 00:22:22.593
We'll need plenty of candles
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

156
00:22:22.718 --> 00:22:26.472
- I'm told he reads all night.
- I'm told he drinks all night.

157
00:22:26.597 --> 00:22:29.767
How much could he possibly drink?
A man of his...

158
00:22:29.892 --> 00:22:31.435
stature?

159
00:22:31.561 --> 00:22:34.438
We've brought up eight barrels of ale
from the cellar.

160
00:22:34.564 --> 00:22:35.773
Perhaps we'll find out.

161
00:22:35.898 --> 00:22:37.733
In any case. candles.

162
00:22:43.865 --> 00:22:46.784
Why is your mother so dead set on us
getting pretty for the king?

163
00:22:46.909 --> 00:22:49.662
It's for the queen. I bet.
I hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

164
00:22:49.787 --> 00:22:51.831
I hear the prince is a right royal prick.

165
00:22:51.956 --> 00:22:55.418
Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab
with his right royal prick.

166
00:22:57.336 --> 00:22:59.463
Go on. Tommy. shear him good.

167
00:22:59.589 --> 00:23:01.883
He's never met a girl he likes better
than his own hair.

168
00:23:38.878 --> 00:23:41.547
Gods. but they grow fast.

169
00:23:44.008 --> 00:23:45.509
Brandon!

170
00:23:45.635 --> 00:23:48.638
I saw the king.
He's got hundreds of people.

171
00:23:48.763 --> 00:23:51.849
How many times have I told you?
No climbing.

172
00:23:51.974 --> 00:23:54.936
But he's coming right now. down our road.

173
00:24:01.943 --> 00:24:04.362
I want you to promise me.

174
00:24:04.487 --> 00:24:06.155
no more climbing.

175
00:24:10.993 --> 00:24:12.161
I promise.

176
00:24:14.330 --> 00:24:17.375
- Do you know what?
- What?

177
00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:19.710
You always look at your feet
before you lie.

178
00:24:21.879 --> 00:24:23.631
Run and find your father.

179
00:24:23.756 --> 00:24:25.800
Tell him the king is close.

180
00:25:10.219 --> 00:25:13.597
Where's Arya?
Sansa. where's your sister?

181
00:25:23.899 --> 00:25:26.068
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.
- Oh.

182
00:25:26.193 --> 00:25:28.112
What are you doing with that on?

183
00:25:30.531 --> 00:25:32.616
- Go on.
-

184
00:25:33.993 --> 00:25:35.661
Move!

185
00:26:57.827 --> 00:26:59.662
Your Grace.

186
00:27:04.166 --> 00:27:05.835
You've got fat.

187
00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:19.473
- Cat!
- Your Grace.

188
00:27:23.602 --> 00:27:27.064
Nine years... Why haven't I seen you?
Where the hell have you been?

189
00:27:27.189 --> 00:27:30.734
Guarding the North for you. Your Grace.
Winterfell is yours.

190
00:27:34.655 --> 00:27:37.199
- Where's the Imp?
- Will you shut up?

191
00:27:37.324 --> 00:27:38.826
Who have we here?

192
00:27:40.202 --> 00:27:41.537
You must be Robb.

193
00:27:44.498 --> 00:27:46.625
My. you're a pretty one.

194
00:27:48.043 --> 00:27:49.920
Your name is?

195
00:27:50.045 --> 00:27:51.422
Arya.

196
00:27:52.631 --> 00:27:55.217
Oh. show us your muscles.

197
00:27:56.552 --> 00:27:58.846
You'll be a soldier.

198
00:28:01.724 --> 00:28:04.143
That's Jaime Lannister.
the queen's twin brother.

199
00:28:04.268 --> 00:28:06.395
Would you please shut up?

200
00:28:15.946 --> 00:28:16.947
My queen.

201
00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:19.825
My queen.

202
00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:21.952
Take me to your crypt.
I want to pay my respects.

203
00:28:22.077 --> 00:28:23.913
We've been riding for a month. my love.

204
00:28:24.413 --> 00:28:26.040
Surely the dead can wait.

205
00:28:26.165 --> 00:28:28.042
Ned.

206
00:28:37.718 --> 00:28:38.928
Where's the Imp?

207
00:28:42.431 --> 00:28:44.433
Where is our brother?

208
00:28:44.558 --> 00:28:46.310
Go and find the little beast.

209
00:28:48.687 --> 00:28:50.356
Tell me about Jon Arryn.

210
00:28:51.607 --> 00:28:53.817
One minute he was fine and then...

211
00:28:55.027 --> 00:28:57.780
burned right through him.
whatever it was.

212
00:28:58.948 --> 00:29:00.950
I loved that man.

213
00:29:01.075 --> 00:29:02.409
We both did.

214
00:29:02.534 --> 00:29:06.872
He never had to teach you much.
but me? You remember me at 16?

215
00:29:06.997 --> 00:29:08.832
All I wanted to do

216
00:29:08.958 --> 00:29:11.585
was crack skulls and fuck girls.

217
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:14.838
- He showed me what was what.
- Aye.

218
00:29:14.964 --> 00:29:17.591
Don't look at me like that.
It's not his fault I didn't listen.

219
00:29:22.137 --> 00:29:24.181
I need you. Ned.

220
00:29:24.306 --> 00:29:27.977
down at King's Landing. not up here
where you're no damn use to anybody.

221
00:29:29.853 --> 00:29:31.647
Lord Eddard Stark...

222
00:29:32.606 --> 00:29:35.067
I would name you the Hand of the King.

223
00:29:39.530 --> 00:29:41.657
I'm not worthy of the honor.

224
00:29:41.782 --> 00:29:43.200
I'm not trying to honor you.

225
00:29:43.325 --> 00:29:45.035
I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

226
00:29:45.160 --> 00:29:48.872
while I eat. drink and whore my way
to an early grave.

227
00:29:48.998 --> 00:29:50.833
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

228
00:29:52.376 --> 00:29:54.336
You helped me win the Iron Throne.

229
00:29:54.461 --> 00:29:57.172
now help me keep the damn thing.

230
00:29:57.298 --> 00:29:59.675
We were meant to rule together.

231
00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:03.637
If your sister had lived.
we'd have been bound by blood.

232
00:30:04.596 --> 00:30:06.181
Well. it's not too late.

233
00:30:07.850 --> 00:30:09.518
I have a son.
you have a daughter.

234
00:30:11.353 --> 00:30:13.022
Well join our houses.

235
00:30:38.213 --> 00:30:41.175
It is true what they say
about the northern girls.

236
00:30:49.391 --> 00:30:51.727
Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

237
00:30:51.852 --> 00:30:53.479
I did hear something about that.

238
00:30:53.604 --> 00:30:55.773
And the queen and her twin brother.

239
00:30:55.898 --> 00:30:58.942
They say that he is the most handsome man
in the Seven Kingdoms.

240
00:30:59.068 --> 00:31:00.944
And the other brother?

241
00:31:01.070 --> 00:31:04.281
- The queen has two brothers?
- There's the pretty one...

242
00:31:05.491 --> 00:31:07.201
and there's the clever one.

243
00:31:08.494 --> 00:31:09.995
Mmm...

244
00:31:10.120 --> 00:31:12.373
I hear they call him the Imp.

245
00:31:12.498 --> 00:31:14.291
I hear he hates that nickname.

246
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:17.795
Oh? I hear he's more than earned it.

247
00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:20.172
I hear he's a drunken little lecher.

248
00:31:20.297 --> 00:31:22.758
prone to all manner of perversions.

249
00:31:22.883 --> 00:31:24.676
Clever girl.

250
00:31:26.428 --> 00:31:28.263
We've been expecting you. Lord Tyrion.

251
00:31:29.598 --> 00:31:31.183
Have you?

252
00:31:31.308 --> 00:31:32.684
- Already?
- Oh!

253
00:31:35.604 --> 00:31:38.315
- The gods gave me one blessing.
-

254
00:31:43.195 --> 00:31:45.697
- Don't get up.
- My lord.

255
00:31:45.823 --> 00:31:49.493
Should I explain to you the meaning of
a closed door in a whorehouse. brother?

256
00:31:49.618 --> 00:31:51.662
You have much to teach me. no doubt.

257
00:31:51.787 --> 00:31:54.957
but our sister craves your attention.

258
00:31:55.666 --> 00:31:57.668
She has odd cravings. our sister.

259
00:31:57.793 --> 00:31:59.837
A family trait.

260
00:31:59.962 --> 00:32:02.423
Now. the Starks are feasting us at Sundown.

261
00:32:03.424 --> 00:32:07.386
- Don't leave me alone with these people.
- I'm sorry. I've begun the feast a bit early.

262
00:32:07.511 --> 00:32:10.848
And this is the first of many courses.

263
00:32:10.973 --> 00:32:13.183
I thought you might say that.

264
00:32:13.308 --> 00:32:15.936
But since we're short on time...

265
00:32:16.061 --> 00:32:17.354
Come on. girls.

266
00:32:23.318 --> 00:32:25.112
See you at sundown.

267
00:32:25.237 --> 00:32:27.322
Close the door!

268
00:32:39.751 --> 00:32:42.504
Did you have to bury her
in a place like this?

269
00:32:44.381 --> 00:32:46.592
She should be on a hill somewhere

270
00:32:46.717 --> 00:32:49.052
with the sun and the clouds above her.

271
00:32:49.178 --> 00:32:51.221
She was my sister.

272
00:32:51.346 --> 00:32:53.015
This is where she belongs.

273
00:32:54.183 --> 00:32:56.518
She belonged with me.

274
00:33:01.982 --> 00:33:05.194
In my dreams.
I kill him every night.

275
00:33:06.737 --> 00:33:11.033
It's done. Your Grace.
The Targaryens are gone.

276
00:33:14.244 --> 00:33:16.163
Not all of them.

277
00:33:27.090 --> 00:33:29.051
Daenerys!

278
00:33:32.221 --> 00:33:33.931
Daenerys.

279
00:33:34.056 --> 00:33:36.058
There's our bride-to-be.

280
00:33:37.059 --> 00:33:39.645
Look. a gift from Illyrio.

281
00:33:41.230 --> 00:33:42.814
Touch it.

282
00:33:42.940 --> 00:33:45.150
Go on. feel the fabric.

283
00:33:50.072 --> 00:33:51.073
Mmm.

284
00:33:53.242 --> 00:33:55.077
Isn't he a gracious host?

285
00:33:58.455 --> 00:34:02.125
We've been his guests for over a year
and he's never asked us for anything.

286
00:34:02.251 --> 00:34:04.127
IIlyrio's no fool.

287
00:34:04.253 --> 00:34:06.046
He knows I won't forget my friends

288
00:34:06.171 --> 00:34:08.423
when I come into my throne.

289
00:34:12.761 --> 00:34:14.513
You still slouch.

290
00:34:18.892 --> 00:34:21.186
Let them see.

291
00:34:23.981 --> 00:34:26.733
You have a woman's body now.

292
00:34:44.626 --> 00:34:46.628
I need you to be perfect today.

293
00:34:49.172 --> 00:34:50.549
Can you do that for me?

294
00:34:54.094 --> 00:34:56.680
You don't want to wake the dragon. do you?

295
00:34:58.640 --> 00:34:59.683
No.

296
00:35:06.815 --> 00:35:09.401
When they write the history
of my reign. sweet sister.

297
00:35:09.526 --> 00:35:11.486
they will say it began today.

298
00:35:35.218 --> 00:35:36.887
It's too hot. my lady.

299
00:35:58.158 --> 00:36:00.077
Where is he?

300
00:36:00.202 --> 00:36:03.080
The Dothraki are not known
for their punctuality.

301
00:36:20.555 --> 00:36:22.474
May I present my honored guests?

302
00:36:22.599 --> 00:36:26.144
Viserys of House Targaryen.

303
00:36:26.269 --> 00:36:27.771
the third of his name.

304
00:36:27.896 --> 00:36:31.274
the rightful King of the Andals
and the First Men.

305
00:36:31.400 --> 00:36:32.693
and his sister.

306
00:36:32.818 --> 00:36:35.696
Daenerys of House Targaryen.

307
00:36:38.740 --> 00:36:41.159
Do you see how long his hair is?

308
00:36:41.284 --> 00:36:44.079
When Dothraki are defeated in combat

309
00:36:44.204 --> 00:36:47.791
they cut off their braid
so the whole world can see their shame.

310
00:36:47.916 --> 00:36:51.753
Khal Drogo has never been defeated.

311
00:36:53.213 --> 00:36:57.092
He's a savage. of course.
but he's one of the finest killers alive.

312
00:36:58.468 --> 00:37:00.595
And you will be his queen.

313
00:37:01.388 --> 00:37:03.265
Come forward. my dear.

314
00:37:43.388 --> 00:37:44.514
Where is he going?

315
00:37:44.639 --> 00:37:47.350
- The ceremony is over.
- But he... But he didn't say anything.

316
00:37:47.476 --> 00:37:48.602
Did he like her?

317
00:37:48.727 --> 00:37:52.481
Trust me. Your Grace.
if he didn't like her. we'd know.

318
00:37:55.609 --> 00:37:57.861
It won't be long now.

319
00:37:57.986 --> 00:38:01.615
Soon you will cross the narrow sea
and take back your father's throne.

320
00:38:02.866 --> 00:38:06.703
The people drink secret toasts
to your health.

321
00:38:06.828 --> 00:38:09.289
They cry out for their true king.

322
00:38:12.834 --> 00:38:14.711
When will they be married?

323
00:38:14.836 --> 00:38:18.381
Soon.
The Dothraki never stay still for long.

324
00:38:18.507 --> 00:38:20.759
Is it true they lie with their horses?

325
00:38:21.510 --> 00:38:23.804
I wouldn't ask Khal Drogo.

326
00:38:23.929 --> 00:38:26.056
Do you take me for a fool?

327
00:38:26.181 --> 00:38:27.891
I take you for a king.

328
00:38:28.016 --> 00:38:31.144
Kings lack the caution
of common men.

329
00:38:31.269 --> 00:38:32.979
My apologies if I've given offense.

330
00:38:33.104 --> 00:38:35.690
I know how to play a man like Drogo.

331
00:38:35.816 --> 00:38:38.610
I give him a queen
and he gives me an army.

332
00:38:39.528 --> 00:38:41.571
I don't want to be his queen.

333
00:38:46.660 --> 00:38:48.036
I want to go home.

334
00:38:48.703 --> 00:38:50.038
So do I.

335
00:38:51.206 --> 00:38:53.500
I want us both to go home.

336
00:38:53.625 --> 00:38:55.836
but they took it from us.

337
00:38:55.961 --> 00:38:57.754
So tell me. sweet sister.

338
00:38:57.879 --> 00:38:59.548
how do we go home?

339
00:39:02.259 --> 00:39:03.426
I don't know.

340
00:39:03.552 --> 00:39:05.804
We go home with an army.

341
00:39:07.889 --> 00:39:10.183
With Khal Drogo's army.

342
00:39:11.393 --> 00:39:14.396
I would let his whole tribe fuck you.

343
00:39:14.521 --> 00:39:17.607
all 40.000 men and their horses too.

344
00:39:17.732 --> 00:39:19.401
if that's what it took.

345
00:39:36.710 --> 00:39:39.212
Do you think Joffrey will like me?

346
00:39:39.337 --> 00:39:41.548
What if he thinks I'm ugly?

347
00:39:41.673 --> 00:39:45.093
Then he is the stupidest prince that ever lived.

348
00:39:47.762 --> 00:39:49.097
He's so handsome.

349
00:39:50.265 --> 00:39:52.976
When would we be married?
Soon? Or do we have to wait?

350
00:39:53.101 --> 00:39:56.187
Hush now.
Your father hasn't even said yes.

351
00:39:56.313 --> 00:39:57.981
Why would he say no?

352
00:39:58.106 --> 00:40:01.026
He'd be the second most powerful man
in the kingdoms.

353
00:40:01.151 --> 00:40:03.194
He'd have to leave home.

354
00:40:04.487 --> 00:40:06.865
He'd have to leave me.

355
00:40:07.866 --> 00:40:09.993
And so would you.

356
00:40:10.118 --> 00:40:12.454
You left your home to come here.

357
00:40:12.579 --> 00:40:14.331
And I'd be queen someday.

358
00:40:16.291 --> 00:40:17.834
Please make Father say yes!

359
00:40:17.959 --> 00:40:19.753
- Sansa...
- Please. please!

360
00:40:19.878 --> 00:40:22.756
It's the only thing I ever wanted.

361
00:40:36.645 --> 00:40:38.813
Fill that up!
Boys. Rodrik. come on.

362
00:40:38.939 --> 00:40:40.982
Come on!

363
00:40:41.107 --> 00:40:43.860
Come here. you little beauty!

364
00:40:59.668 --> 00:41:00.961
Is he dead yet?

365
00:41:06.424 --> 00:41:07.509
Uncle Benjen.

366
00:41:10.512 --> 00:41:11.721
You got bigger.

367
00:41:13.098 --> 00:41:14.683
Rode all day.

368
00:41:14.808 --> 00:41:17.394
Didn't want to leave you alone
with the Lannisters.

369
00:41:17.519 --> 00:41:18.853
Why aren't you at the feast?

370
00:41:18.979 --> 00:41:21.731
Lady Stark thought it might
insult the royal family

371
00:41:21.856 --> 00:41:23.775
to seat a bastard in their midst.

372
00:41:24.609 --> 00:41:26.987
Well. you're always
welcome on the Wall.

373
00:41:27.112 --> 00:41:29.072
No bastard was ever
refused a seat there.

374
00:41:29.197 --> 00:41:30.907
So take me with you
when you go back.

375
00:41:31.032 --> 00:41:33.910
- Jon...
- Father will let me if you ask him.

376
00:41:34.035 --> 00:41:35.829
I know he will.

377
00:41:38.540 --> 00:41:40.625
The Wall isn't going anywhere.

378
00:41:40.750 --> 00:41:43.420
I'm ready to swear your oath.

379
00:41:43.545 --> 00:41:46.673
You don't understand
what you'd be giving up.

380
00:41:46.798 --> 00:41:48.717
We have no families.

381
00:41:48.842 --> 00:41:52.554
- None of us will ever father sons.
- I don't care about that.

382
00:41:52.679 --> 00:41:55.640
You might. if you knew what it meant.

383
00:41:59.019 --> 00:42:01.479
I'd better get inside.

384
00:42:01.604 --> 00:42:03.898
rescue your father from his guests.

385
00:42:06.943 --> 00:42:08.987
Weill talk later.

386
00:42:17.412 --> 00:42:19.748
Your uncle's in the Night's Watch.

387
00:42:22.709 --> 00:42:25.045
What are you doing back there?

388
00:42:25.170 --> 00:42:27.380
Preparing for a night with your family.

389
00:42:32.594 --> 00:42:34.512
I've always wanted to see the Wall.

390
00:42:34.637 --> 00:42:36.431
You're Tyrion Lannister.

391
00:42:36.556 --> 00:42:38.099
the queen's brother?

392
00:42:38.224 --> 00:42:39.893
My greatest accomplishment.

393
00:42:41.436 --> 00:42:44.105
And you. you're Ned Stark's bastard.
aren't you?

394
00:42:47.567 --> 00:42:49.736
Did I offend you? Sorry.

395
00:42:51.863 --> 00:42:54.324
You are the bastard. though.

396
00:42:55.617 --> 00:42:57.952
Lord Eddard Stark is my father.

397
00:42:59.204 --> 00:43:01.831
And Lady Stark is not your mother.

398
00:43:01.956 --> 00:43:04.959
making you...the bastard.

399
00:43:06.461 --> 00:43:09.089
Let me give you some advice. bastard.

400
00:43:10.256 --> 00:43:12.050
Never forget what you are.

401
00:43:12.175 --> 00:43:14.511
The rest of the world will not.

402
00:43:14.636 --> 00:43:16.221
Wear it like armor...

403
00:43:17.013 --> 00:43:19.307
and it can never be used to hurt you.

404
00:43:20.975 --> 00:43:23.645
What the hell do you know
about being a bastard?

405
00:43:26.106 --> 00:43:28.566
All dwarves are bastards
in their father's eyes.

406
00:43:50.255 --> 00:43:51.881
You at a feast...

407
00:43:52.841 --> 00:43:54.509
it's like a bear in a trap.

408
00:43:56.511 --> 00:43:58.096
The boy I beheaded...

409
00:43:59.430 --> 00:44:02.350
- did you know him?
- Of course I did. Just a lad.

410
00:44:03.518 --> 00:44:05.603
But he was tough. Ned.

411
00:44:05.728 --> 00:44:06.980
a true ranger.

412
00:44:08.731 --> 00:44:10.483
He was talking madness.

413
00:44:11.693 --> 00:44:13.444
Said the walkers slaughtered his friends.

414
00:44:13.570 --> 00:44:15.864
The two he was with are still missing.

415
00:44:17.532 --> 00:44:20.994
Hmph. A wildling ambush.

416
00:44:21.995 --> 00:44:23.079
Maybe.

417
00:44:24.372 --> 00:44:26.916
Direwolves south of the Wall.

418
00:44:27.041 --> 00:44:29.252
talk of the walkers.

419
00:44:29.377 --> 00:44:31.921
and my brother might be
the next Hand of the King.

420
00:44:33.131 --> 00:44:34.966
Winter is coming.

421
00:44:36.593 --> 00:44:38.386
Winter is coming.

422
00:44:40.054 --> 00:44:42.891
- Uncle Benjen.
- Robb boy.

423
00:44:43.016 --> 00:44:44.475
- How are you?
- I'm good.

424
00:44:47.937 --> 00:44:50.690
Is this your first time
in the North. Your Grace?

425
00:44:50.815 --> 00:44:53.568
Yes. Lovely country.

426
00:44:57.363 --> 00:45:00.700
I'm sure it's very grim
after King's Landing.

427
00:45:01.993 --> 00:45:06.372
I remember how scared I was when
Ned brought me up here for the first time.

428
00:45:08.583 --> 00:45:10.168
Hello. little dove.

429
00:45:11.169 --> 00:45:13.338
But you are a beauty.

430
00:45:13.463 --> 00:45:15.757
- How old are you?
- Thirteen. Your Grace.

431
00:45:15.882 --> 00:45:18.468
You're tall. Still growing?

432
00:45:18.593 --> 00:45:20.428
I think so. Your Grace.

433
00:45:20.553 --> 00:45:22.680
And have you bled yet?

434
00:45:27.810 --> 00:45:29.270
No. Your Grace.

435
00:45:30.772 --> 00:45:32.398
Your dress. did you make it?

436
00:45:34.192 --> 00:45:37.445
Such talent.
You must make something for me.

437
00:45:39.364 --> 00:45:42.408
I hear we might share
a grandchild someday.

438
00:45:43.451 --> 00:45:44.619
I hear the same.

439
00:45:44.744 --> 00:45:46.955
Your daughter will do well in the capital.

440
00:45:47.080 --> 00:45:50.416
Such a beauty shouldn't stay
hidden up here forever.

441
00:46:07.433 --> 00:46:10.061
- Your pardon.
- I hear we might be neighbors soon.

442
00:46:10.186 --> 00:46:13.648
- I hope it's true.
- Yes. the king has honored me with his offer.

443
00:46:13.773 --> 00:46:16.985
I'm sure we'll have a tournament to celebrate
your new title. if you accept.

444
00:46:17.110 --> 00:46:19.195
It would be good
to have you on the field.

445
00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:21.698
The competition has become a bit stale.

446
00:46:21.823 --> 00:46:24.075
- I don't fight in tournaments.
- No?

447
00:46:24.200 --> 00:46:25.743
Getting a little old for it?

448
00:46:27.704 --> 00:46:29.747
I don't fight in tournaments

449
00:46:29.872 --> 00:46:32.250
because when I fight a man for real.

450
00:46:32.375 --> 00:46:34.127
I don't want him to know what I can do.

451
00:46:36.421 --> 00:46:37.797
Well said.

452
00:46:39.173 --> 00:46:40.508
Arya!

453
00:46:42.844 --> 00:46:44.554
It's not funny!

454
00:46:44.679 --> 00:46:47.307
She always does this.

455
00:46:47.432 --> 00:46:49.851
This was my favorite dress
and she ruined it.

456
00:46:49.976 --> 00:46:52.437
She always does it
and it's not funny!

457
00:46:52.562 --> 00:46:54.397
Time for bed.

458
00:47:05.491 --> 00:47:07.160
I'm a Northman.

459
00:47:08.870 --> 00:47:13.374
I belong here with you. not down south
in that rats' nest they call a capital.

460
00:47:14.417 --> 00:47:17.170
I won't let him take you.

461
00:47:18.713 --> 00:47:21.299
The king takes what he wants.

462
00:47:21.424 --> 00:47:23.718
That's why he's king.

463
00:47:24.761 --> 00:47:28.431
I'll say. "Listen. fat man."

464
00:47:29.724 --> 00:47:32.852
"You are not taking
my husband anywhere.

465
00:47:32.977 --> 00:47:34.896
"He belongs to me now."

466
00:47:38.649 --> 00:47:40.693
How did he get so fat?

467
00:47:40.818 --> 00:47:45.114
He only stops eating
when it's time for a drink.

468
00:47:46.741 --> 00:47:49.160
It's Maester Luwin. my lord.

469
00:47:50.620 --> 00:47:52.538
Send him in.

470
00:47:54.832 --> 00:47:57.168
Pardon. my lord. my lady.

471
00:47:57.293 --> 00:47:59.796
A rider in the night...

472
00:47:59.921 --> 00:48:02.090
from your sister.

473
00:48:09.806 --> 00:48:12.433
- Stay.
- This was sent from the Eyrie.

474
00:48:18.439 --> 00:48:20.691
What's she doing at the Eyrie?

475
00:48:20.817 --> 00:48:23.361
She hasn't been back there
since her wedding.

476
00:48:31.828 --> 00:48:33.704
What news?

477
00:48:35.331 --> 00:48:37.792
She's fled the capital.

478
00:48:40.128 --> 00:48:42.672
She says Jon Arryn was murdered.

479
00:48:42.797 --> 00:48:44.674
By the Lannisters.

480
00:48:44.799 --> 00:48:47.468
She says the king is in danger.

481
00:48:47.593 --> 00:48:49.846
She's fresh widowed. Cat.

482
00:48:49.971 --> 00:48:51.597
She doesn't know what she's saying.

483
00:48:51.722 --> 00:48:57.019
Lysa's head would be on a spike right now
if the wrong people had found that letter.

484
00:48:57.145 --> 00:48:59.313
Do you think she would risk her life.

485
00:48:59.439 --> 00:49:01.023
her son's life.

486
00:49:01.149 --> 00:49:04.527
if she wasn't certain
her husband was murdered?

487
00:49:11.742 --> 00:49:13.619
If this news is true...

488
00:49:13.744 --> 00:49:17.290
and the Lannisters conspire
against the throne.

489
00:49:17.415 --> 00:49:19.834
who but you can protect the king?

490
00:49:19.959 --> 00:49:22.211
They murdered the last Hand.

491
00:49:22.336 --> 00:49:24.547
Now you want Ned to take the job?

492
00:49:24.672 --> 00:49:28.551
The king rode for a month
to ask for Lord Stark's help.

493
00:49:28.676 --> 00:49:31.179
He's the only one he trusts.

494
00:49:32.680 --> 00:49:35.516
You swore the king an oath. my lord.

495
00:49:35.641 --> 00:49:39.228
He's spent half his life
fighting Robert's wars.

496
00:49:39.353 --> 00:49:41.355
He owes him nothing.

497
00:49:43.274 --> 00:49:46.486
Your father and brother
rode south once

498
00:49:46.611 --> 00:49:49.238
on a king's demand.

499
00:49:51.157 --> 00:49:53.284
A different time.

500
00:49:54.660 --> 00:49:56.746
A different king.

501
00:50:57.932 --> 00:51:01.435
When do I meet with the khal?
We need to begin planning the invasion.

502
00:51:01.561 --> 00:51:04.981
If Knhal Drogo has promised you a crown.
you shall have it.

503
00:51:05.106 --> 00:51:08.150
- When?
- When their omens favor war.

504
00:51:09.277 --> 00:51:11.821
I piss on Dothraki omens.

505
00:51:11.946 --> 00:51:14.615
I've waited 17 years to get my throne back.

506
00:52:14.550 --> 00:52:19.513
A Dothraki wedding without at least
three deaths is considered a dull affair.

507
00:52:41.869 --> 00:52:44.914
A small gift. for the new khaleesi.

508
00:52:45.873 --> 00:52:48.459
Songs and histories from the Seven Kingdoms.

509
00:52:50.127 --> 00:52:51.545
Thank you. ser.

510
00:52:53.255 --> 00:52:55.925
Are you from my country?

511
00:52:56.050 --> 00:52:58.094
Ser Jorah Mormont of Bear Island.

512
00:52:58.219 --> 00:53:00.930
I served your father for many years.

513
00:53:01.055 --> 00:53:04.016
Gods be good. I hope to
always serve the rightful king.

514
00:53:27.248 --> 00:53:29.917
Dragon's eggs. Daenerys.

515
00:53:30.042 --> 00:53:32.795
from the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai.

516
00:53:32.920 --> 00:53:35.840
The ages have turned them to stone.

517
00:53:35.965 --> 00:53:37.925
but they will always be beautiful.

518
00:53:40.177 --> 00:53:41.846
Thank you. Magister.

519
00:54:50.539 --> 00:54:52.583
She's beautiful.

520
00:54:56.837 --> 00:54:58.088
Ser Jorah. I...

521
